  "texts": [
    "The bottlenecks of traditional object detection algorithms in practical applications are twofold.",
    "On the one hand, because the traditional object detection algorithm requires the designer to extract the features of the sample using prior knowledge, only a few parameters can appear in the feature design to lessen the difficulty of manually tuning the parameters.",
    "Shallow classifiers, on the other hand, require exponentially more parameters and training data in the face of tough detection tasks due to the lack of model depth.",
    "In response to the problem of manual parameter tuning of traditional object detection algorithms, the research boom in deep networks has brought new opportunities for the development of object detection.",
    "Compared with traditional 99 Page 26 of 43 object detection algorithms, deep CNN can automatically learn feature representations of parameters from massive data sets and do not require additional training classifiers, which greatly improves the efficiency of the feature learning process."
  ],
